Too Young to Die Once I was four years old, i told my mama &ldquo;Pretty woman walking down the streah haha&rdquo; Then she shouted at me and i said mama &ldquo;You ugly woman, yacking down the stream yah&rdquo;
That was then and the world was smaller And everything was so simpler and life was gentler My brother and I were running down the roads in Sodnac Drinking our dad&rsquo;s secret stash of cognac

From Lab Success to Production By May 2000, our Wi-Fi experiments from 1999 had proven successful enough that NTU was considering a campus-wide deployment. This wasn&rsquo;t just about adding more access points; it was about understanding how wireless networks could scale from experimental hobby to critical infrastructure.
The challenge shifted from &ldquo;can we do this?&rdquo; to &ldquo;how do we do this reliably for hundreds of users simultaneously?&rdquo;
Scaling Wireless Networks I spent weeks scaling solutions, grappling with the complexities of managing a distributed network of access points.
